WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:09.009
{\an8}(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:56.222
{\an8}â™ª

3
00:01:49.734 --> 00:01:51.903
(music fades out)

4
00:01:56.408 --> 00:01:59.619
(tense. solemn music playing)

5
00:02:06.292 --> 00:02:07.919
(footsteps approach)

6
00:02:23.601 --> 00:02:25.603
â™ª

7
00:02:35.447 --> 00:02:37.032
(inhales)

8
00:02:45.123 --> 00:02:47.125
â™ª

9
00:03:00.388 --> 00:03:03.391
- (bell tolling)
- (street chatter)

10
00:03:09.981 --> 00:03:12.772
- Only one.
- That's enough. stand back.

11
00:03:12.776 --> 00:03:15.816
- (chatter continues)
- (distant horn blowing)

12
00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.739
(bell tolling)

13
00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:21.697
knight: Behold!

14
00:03:21.701 --> 00:03:24.950
The traitor dragon Meleys!

15
00:03:24.954 --> 00:03:28.996
- (crowd clamoring)
- Slain at Rook's Rest

16
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.669
by your king!

17
00:03:32.754 --> 00:03:34.377
To Aegon!

18
00:03:34.381 --> 00:03:37.425
(tense music playing)

19
00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:43.094
(crowd murmuring)

20
00:03:43.098 --> 00:03:44.933
- It can't be...
- They killed a dragon!

21
00:03:46.393 --> 00:03:49.187
Towns person 1: Mark my
words. this is a black omen.

22
00:03:53.566 --> 00:03:55.568
â™ª

23
00:04:04.786 --> 00:04:07.034
- (bell tolling)
- (horse neighs)

24
00:04:07.038 --> 00:04:09.457
towns person 2: Rhaenyra
will answer this.

25
00:04:10.542 --> 00:04:12.043
'Tis an abomination.

26
00:04:13.294 --> 00:04:15.547
Don't they realize
we won the battle?

27
00:04:16.548 --> 00:04:18.550
Strange victory...

28
00:04:19.467 --> 00:04:21.090
if it was one.

29
00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:23.138
â™ª

30
00:04:31.896 --> 00:04:33.481
(crowd chattering)

31
00:04:38.403 --> 00:04:40.572
- (horn blowing)
- knight: Behold!

32
00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:44.739
The traitor dragon Meleys!

33
00:04:44.743 --> 00:04:46.532
I thought the dragons was gods.

34
00:04:46.536 --> 00:04:49.910
Knight: Slain at Rook's
Rest by your king!

35
00:04:49.914 --> 00:04:52.500
â™ª

36
00:04:58.256 --> 00:04:59.924
It's just meat.

37
00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:03.303
â™ª

38
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:18.026
(bell tolling)

39
00:05:31.164 --> 00:05:33.792
â™ª

40
00:05:53.144 --> 00:05:55.146
(solemn music playing)

41
00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:19.838
â™ª

42
00:06:39.441 --> 00:06:41.443
(music softens)

43
00:07:11.806 --> 00:07:13.808
â™ª

44
00:07:14.893 --> 00:07:16.895
{\an8}(quiet chattering)

45
00:07:19.564 --> 00:07:20.770
Is he alive?

46
00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.938
His Grace...

47
00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:25.737
remains with us. for the moment.

48
00:07:30.241 --> 00:07:32.452
(music fades out)

49
00:07:33.328 --> 00:07:35.701
(quiet chattering)

50
00:07:35.705 --> 00:07:39.334
- (Aegon breathing heavily)
- (tools clinking)

51
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.673
(pus squelching)

52
00:08:04.109 --> 00:08:06.319
(pus squelching)

53
00:08:08.488 --> 00:08:10.115
(grunting)

54
00:08:18.289 --> 00:08:21.167
(quiet chattering)

55
00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:23.958
Is my son going to die?

56
00:08:23.962 --> 00:08:25.922
I'm afraid I cannot say.

57
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:29.296
Now. if you'll excuse me. Your Grace.
these next hours are most critical.

58
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.090
Of course.

59
00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:34.139
(solemn music playing)

60
00:08:36.725 --> 00:08:38.727
(quiet chattering)

61
00:08:41.896 --> 00:08:43.189
(bone cracks)

62
00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:45.128
Grand Maester Orwyle:
Easy as you can.

63
00:08:49.404 --> 00:08:51.656
â™ª

64
00:09:00.331 --> 00:09:02.334
(strained breathing)

65
00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:08.048
Someone will have to
rule in his stead.

66
00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:22.058
(music softens)

67
00:09:22.062 --> 00:09:23.730
(footsteps approach)

68
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:31.525
(birds chirping)

69
00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:34.153
- What happened?
- We took the castle.

70
00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:36.618
At the cost of some 900 men.

71
00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:40.080
So I've heard.

72
00:09:41.873 --> 00:09:44.538
I left a meager garrison
behind to protect it

73
00:09:44.542 --> 00:09:46.999
and the king's dragon.

74
00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:49.543
Sunfyre was long in the dying.

75
00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:52.050
The king. Ser Criston.
what befell him?

76
00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:58.344
His Grace fought valiantly.

77
00:09:58.348 --> 00:10:00.975
(Criston polishing sword)

78
00:10:04.396 --> 00:10:05.726
And Aemond?

79
00:10:05.730 --> 00:10:08.775
- (silence)
- (birds chirping)

80
00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:14.781
What was his part in this?

81
00:10:18.618 --> 00:10:20.620
I could not say.

82
00:10:24.416 --> 00:10:26.835
Alfred Broome: Our largest
dragon has been killed.

83
00:10:28.169 --> 00:10:32.424
Criston Cole marches about
the Crownlands unchallenged.

84
00:10:32.966 --> 00:10:35.927
Duskendale and
Rook's Rest are gone.

85
00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:38.801
We still have no ground army

86
00:10:38.805 --> 00:10:41.804
but the one we hope
that Daemon will raise.

87
00:10:41.808 --> 00:10:46.100
He who has left us...
after some marital spat.

88
00:10:46.104 --> 00:10:47.935
(quiet groans)

89
00:10:47.939 --> 00:10:50.108
Do you take issue
with me. Ser Alfred?

90
00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:54.984
My loyalty to you
is proven. my queen.

91
00:10:54.988 --> 00:10:57.278
Your loyalty. perhaps.

92
00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.114
but your willingness to give
me deference in a time of war.

93
00:11:00.118 --> 00:11:03.325
I could never doubt
your capability.

94
00:11:03.329 --> 00:11:05.957
or your quickness of mind.

95
00:11:07.292 --> 00:11:09.290
It is merely that
the gentler sex.

96
00:11:09.294 --> 00:11:11.625
heretofore. has
not been much privy

97
00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:14.503
to the strategies of battle.

98
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:16.384
or their execution.

99
00:11:18.136 --> 00:11:19.842
There has been peace
in our lifetime.

100
00:11:19.846 --> 00:11:22.307
You've seen no more
battles than I have.

101
00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:35.904
(light. tense music playing)

102
00:11:42.202 --> 00:11:44.784
Send to Maidenpool and
to Crackclaw Point.

103
00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:45.993
Let them man their garrisons

104
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:47.495
and give them stores or weapons

105
00:11:47.499 --> 00:11:48.833
if they find them wanting.

106
00:11:50.168 --> 00:11:51.791
If Cole pursues his campaign.

107
00:11:51.795 --> 00:11:55.169
- our allies must be ready.
- We must answer Rook's Rest.

108
00:11:55.173 --> 00:11:57.338
- and Duskendale.
- Bartimos Celtigar: They are lost already.

109
00:11:57.342 --> 00:11:59.799
But Vhagar is
depleted after such

110
00:11:59.803 --> 00:12:01.008
a hard-fought battle.

111
00:12:01.012 --> 00:12:02.343
Lorent Marbrand:
If Aegon is dead...

112
00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:03.844
Steffon Darklyn: We
will soon know it.

113
00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:05.721
Gormon Massey: 'Twould be
a victory in name only.

114
00:12:05.725 --> 00:12:07.682
They will soon prop up
another in his stead.

115
00:12:07.686 --> 00:12:09.016
Bartimos: The time is ripe.

116
00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:10.476
If we can strike King's Landing

117
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:11.894
before their dragon
is recovered...

118
00:12:11.898 --> 00:12:13.646
Then I myself must do it.

119
00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:17.191
My queen. you are the crown.
It is out of the question.

120
00:12:17.195 --> 00:12:19.694
What would you have me do?

121
00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:21.741
â™ª

122
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:31.376
â™ª

123
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:42.220
Baela Targaryen: Jace?

124
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:46.057
Where are you going?

125
00:12:47.642 --> 00:12:51.146
To Harrenhal. To
treat with Daemon.

126
00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:53.227
Rhaenys is fallen.

127
00:12:53.231 --> 00:12:55.104
He must affirm his
loyalty to my mother

128
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:56.985
and report his standing.

129
00:12:59.904 --> 00:13:02.278
And you think you
will tame him...

130
00:13:02.282 --> 00:13:03.904
when the queen
herself could not?

131
00:13:03.908 --> 00:13:06.782
My mother gladly sends you away

132
00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:08.784
to scout. to fight.

133
00:13:08.788 --> 00:13:11.954
whilst I'm here being forced
to play the coddled princeling.

134
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:16.125
- It's humiliating. Baela.
- She only protects you.

135
00:13:16.129 --> 00:13:17.752
You are the succession.

136
00:13:17.756 --> 00:13:21.593
Then I must be seen to act
for her claim and mine.

137
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:27.849
I can sit still no longer.

138
00:13:30.477 --> 00:13:31.978
I must act.

139
00:13:39.611 --> 00:13:40.945
The Freys.

140
00:13:43.198 --> 00:13:45.738
They control the
crossing at the Twins.

141
00:13:45.742 --> 00:13:48.491
Cregan Stark's graybeards
are marching south.

142
00:13:48.495 --> 00:13:51.952
If his men had a direct
route into the Riverlands.

143
00:13:51.956 --> 00:13:54.664
we would not have to
wait for Daemon to act.

144
00:13:54.668 --> 00:13:57.333
I will treat with The
Freys to secure it.

145
00:13:57.337 --> 00:13:59.005
She will not like it.

146
00:13:59.673 --> 00:14:03.301
Then don't tell her.
Not until I'm away.

147
00:14:12.852 --> 00:14:14.854
(Caraxes calls)

148
00:14:16.815 --> 00:14:19.980
{\an8}Daemon Targaryen: The hour is
late and my dragon is hungry.

149
00:14:19.984 --> 00:14:23.317
{\an8}(horses neighing) - You have
no choice but to submit.

150
00:14:23.321 --> 00:14:25.152
Our terms are
simple. Lord Bracken.

151
00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:28.823
Renounce the false
king Aegon as a usurper

152
00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:30.829
and bend the knee to me

153
00:14:31.579 --> 00:14:33.494
or your house burns.

154
00:14:33.498 --> 00:14:36.622
I would sooner be the
Lord of Bones and Cinders

155
00:14:36.626 --> 00:14:40.835
than bend my knee before some
heathen Blackwood cunt...

156
00:14:40.839 --> 00:14:42.628
and his hired dragon.

157
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:44.171
The Brackens were a
people hatched out

158
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:46.799
of the deepest of the
Seven Hells. Your Grace.

159
00:14:46.803 --> 00:14:48.175
It would be a kindness
to oblige them

160
00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:50.177
and send them back
whence they came.

161
00:14:50.181 --> 00:14:51.512
Did your brother's head

162
00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:53.977
keep on its way
back to you. Willem?

163
00:14:54.352 --> 00:14:56.225
I heard the maggots got to it.

164
00:14:56.229 --> 00:14:59.024
That is quite the
impression. Lord Bracken.

165
00:15:00.191 --> 00:15:02.193
But alas. not an answer.

166
00:15:03.778 --> 00:15:05.780
(horses grunting)

167
00:15:07.741 --> 00:15:09.743
(horse neighs)

168
00:15:12.037 --> 00:15:13.371
We choose fire.

169
00:15:14.539 --> 00:15:17.542
- (horse neighs)
- (Caraxes grumbling)

170
00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:27.427
I did not think they
would be so eager to die.

171
00:15:28.386 --> 00:15:30.221
They made their choice.

172
00:15:30.597 --> 00:15:33.596
- You should've indulged them.
- I need them alive.

173
00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:36.519
I came here to raise
swords. not corpses.

174
00:15:37.228 --> 00:15:40.227
But now you see what my house
has known for generations.

175
00:15:40.231 --> 00:15:42.229
They are pigheaded.
intransigent...

176
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:44.778
They would rather
burn than succumb.

177
00:15:48.573 --> 00:15:50.575
Exactly the kind of men I need.

178
00:15:52.786 --> 00:15:54.241
It may yet be possible. I think.

179
00:15:54.245 --> 00:15:56.285
for both of us to
achieve our ends.

180
00:15:56.289 --> 00:15:59.038
We have fought them
for an age and more.

181
00:15:59.042 --> 00:16:00.581
Then perhaps you could try

182
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.796
less fighting and more...

183
00:16:06.466 --> 00:16:08.259
persuading.

184
00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:11.846
They are unyielding in battle.

185
00:16:14.766 --> 00:16:16.768
(wind blowing)

186
00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:20.814
But every man has a weakness.

187
00:16:21.690 --> 00:16:23.942
You take my meaning. then.

188
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:31.533
There are things the crown
itself must not been seen to do.

189
00:16:32.951 --> 00:16:34.740
Show them your worst.

190
00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:36.951
I am your servant. Your Grace.

191
00:16:36.955 --> 00:16:39.958
(tense music playing)

192
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:48.633
(music intensifies)

193
00:16:58.309 --> 00:17:01.934
Jeyne Arryn: <i>Over the
centuries. many and more armies</i>

194
00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:04.983
have broken themselves
against my bloody gate.

195
00:17:07.068 --> 00:17:09.316
(music fades out)

196
00:17:09.320 --> 00:17:11.156
Are you listening?

197
00:17:12.157 --> 00:17:13.988
My lady.

198
00:17:13.992 --> 00:17:16.661
The Eyrie itself is impregnable.

199
00:17:19.080 --> 00:17:22.330
Unless. of course. we're
descended upon from the sky.

200
00:17:22.334 --> 00:17:25.041
You promised the Queen
Rhaenyra 15.000 swords...

201
00:17:25.045 --> 00:17:28.089
In return for
protection. A dragon.

202
00:17:30.008 --> 00:17:32.548
Then she has
exceeded your terms.

203
00:17:32.552 --> 00:17:34.508
She sent two.

204
00:17:34.512 --> 00:17:37.011
Both still wet from the egg.

205
00:17:37.015 --> 00:17:38.016
(scoffs)

206
00:17:38.683 --> 00:17:41.182
I have hunting hounds
that are more fearsome.

207
00:17:41.186 --> 00:17:43.521
They are dragons nonetheless.

208
00:17:44.064 --> 00:17:45.478
I do not recall you specifying

209
00:17:45.482 --> 00:17:47.188
the size of the beast
in your request.

210
00:17:47.192 --> 00:17:49.027
Will you goad me. child?

211
00:17:49.736 --> 00:17:52.530
When your bread and shelter
now depend on my pleasure?

212
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:56.117
The dragons will grow...

213
00:17:57.369 --> 00:17:59.371
- in time.
- I don't have time.

214
00:18:01.206 --> 00:18:03.416
I mislike feeling powerless.

215
00:18:04.876 --> 00:18:06.294
So do I.

216
00:18:12.926 --> 00:18:14.924
This will be your chamber.

217
00:18:14.928 --> 00:18:16.888
I'll expect you at
supper this evening?

218
00:18:20.058 --> 00:18:24.062
My sympathies for the
death of your grandmother.

219
00:18:26.564 --> 00:18:28.566
(wind blowing)

220
00:18:32.278 --> 00:18:35.361
The way they spoke at
my small council today.

221
00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:38.698
Mysaria: Do they hold you responsible
for Rhaenys and her dragon?

222
00:18:38.702 --> 00:18:40.412
I would rather they had.

223
00:18:40.954 --> 00:18:44.203
They speak around me. not to me.

224
00:18:44.207 --> 00:18:45.413
(sighs) They would
make me queen.

225
00:18:45.417 --> 00:18:47.748
but they wish to keep
me here. confined.

226
00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:50.793
They betray their own smallness.

227
00:18:50.797 --> 00:18:52.253
In truth. I cannot fault them.

228
00:18:52.257 --> 00:18:55.301
I am now the sovereign.
I cannot do as I please.

229
00:18:56.428 --> 00:18:59.260
And war has ever
been for men to make.

230
00:18:59.264 --> 00:19:02.596
You are your father's
chosen successor.

231
00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:04.932
He did not prepare me to fight.

232
00:19:04.936 --> 00:19:07.101
If I had been a son.

233
00:19:07.105 --> 00:19:10.525
a sword thrust into my hand
the moment I could walk.

234
00:19:11.192 --> 00:19:13.278
Instead. I was given
my father's cup...

235
00:19:13.987 --> 00:19:16.485
taught the name of
every lord and castle

236
00:19:16.489 --> 00:19:18.237
between Storm's
End and the Twins.

237
00:19:18.241 --> 00:19:21.119
but not the difference
between hilt and foible.

238
00:19:22.037 --> 00:19:23.663
And they know it.

239
00:19:25.373 --> 00:19:28.748
- And Daemon as well...
- Shall your evening meal be served here. Your Grace?

240
00:19:28.752 --> 00:19:30.378
(sharply) Not now.

241
00:19:31.504 --> 00:19:34.507
(distant dragons grumbling)

242
00:19:36.468 --> 00:19:38.053
Will you send to him?

243
00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:42.345
For too long. I have
looked to him for strength.

244
00:19:42.349 --> 00:19:44.513
If I must be supplicant
to my own husband.

245
00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:46.186
what does that make me?

246
00:19:49.856 --> 00:19:52.859
I do not know my part. Mysaria.

247
00:19:55.904 --> 00:19:58.531
The path I walk has
never been trod.

248
00:19:59.866 --> 00:20:03.328
Criston Cole made a mistake.

249
00:20:05.038 --> 00:20:09.205
Parading a dragon's head through
the streets like a prize of war.

250
00:20:09.209 --> 00:20:11.290
but the people see an ill omen.

251
00:20:11.294 --> 00:20:12.875
(scoffs) Yes. as do I.

252
00:20:12.879 --> 00:20:16.045
They are afraid.
bread is scarce.

253
00:20:16.049 --> 00:20:17.672
the king has fallen.

254
00:20:17.676 --> 00:20:20.174
they whisper to each other
that when Viserys lived.

255
00:20:20.178 --> 00:20:22.468
- there was peace.
- (sighs)

256
00:20:22.472 --> 00:20:25.179
But will whispers
tear down stone...

257
00:20:25.183 --> 00:20:26.806
or break shields?

258
00:20:26.810 --> 00:20:30.184
Do not underestimate
your subjects.

259
00:20:30.188 --> 00:20:31.977
They are a thousand-thousand

260
00:20:31.981 --> 00:20:33.646
living in the shadow
of the Red Keep

261
00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:36.857
and forgotten for too long.

262
00:20:36.861 --> 00:20:39.193
And you think they
will turn to me.

263
00:20:39.197 --> 00:20:43.451
To the discontented.
rumors are feed.

264
00:20:44.411 --> 00:20:47.622
(light. tense music playing)

265
00:20:48.123 --> 00:20:49.749
Your Grace.

266
00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:56.381
What you cannot do.
let others do for you.

267
00:20:57.799 --> 00:21:01.048
There is more than one
way to fight a war.

268
00:21:01.052 --> 00:21:03.054
(music intensifies)

269
00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:16.317
â™ª

270
00:21:21.072 --> 00:21:23.279
(music fades out)

271
00:21:23.283 --> 00:21:25.906
Baela: The thought of
her lying in a field.

272
00:21:25.910 --> 00:21:28.496
broken amongst her enemies.

273
00:21:39.174 --> 00:21:43.178
Did your grandmother ever tell you
of the night she claimed Meleys?

274
00:21:44.179 --> 00:21:46.222
She snuck into the Dragonpit.

275
00:21:46.931 --> 00:21:49.392
She knew that place
better than any Elder.

276
00:21:49.934 --> 00:21:51.936
They say she could
see in the dark.

277
00:21:53.605 --> 00:21:55.436
My father was furious.

278
00:21:55.440 --> 00:21:57.480
His own mother's dragon.

279
00:21:57.484 --> 00:21:59.065
the fastest beast ever known.

280
00:21:59.069 --> 00:22:00.983
- and she'd have none of him.
- (Rhaenyra chuckles)

281
00:22:00.987 --> 00:22:03.281
But bent her neck to Rhaenys.

282
00:22:04.324 --> 00:22:06.326
She was fierce...

283
00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:09.662
in love and in anger.

284
00:22:12.374 --> 00:22:16.002
She did not always
care for me. but...

285
00:22:17.796 --> 00:22:21.800
for what she gave me in
the end. I'm grateful.

286
00:22:27.806 --> 00:22:30.642
I wished I had known
her when she was young.

287
00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:40.568
- (chuckles) You are very like her in some ways.
- (Baela chuckles)

288
00:22:43.405 --> 00:22:48.155
And with her gone... I
must rely on you. I think.

289
00:22:48.159 --> 00:22:49.828
Your Grace? (sniffles)

290
00:22:50.995 --> 00:22:53.415
Would you give this
to your grandsire?

291
00:23:05.176 --> 00:23:07.554
I do not wish to stand alone.

292
00:23:09.222 --> 00:23:11.470
(eerie rumbling)

293
00:23:11.474 --> 00:23:13.101
female voice: Daemon.

294
00:23:17.856 --> 00:23:20.146
<i>Daemon.</i>

295
00:23:20.150 --> 00:23:22.777
<i>You were always the strong one.</i>

296
00:23:24.779 --> 00:23:27.407
The finest swordsman...

297
00:23:30.201 --> 00:23:32.871
the fearless dragon rider.

298
00:23:34.748 --> 00:23:37.959
{\an8}<i>Your brother had great
love in his heart...</i>

299
00:23:38.585 --> 00:23:40.628
(heavy breathing)

300
00:23:42.714 --> 00:23:44.966
<i>...but he lacked
your constitution.</i>

301
00:23:46.051 --> 00:23:48.553
<i>Viserys was unsuited
for the crown...</i>

302
00:23:51.806 --> 00:23:55.727
<i>but you... Daemon. you
were made to wear it.</i>

303
00:24:04.069 --> 00:24:06.071
(heavy breathing)

304
00:24:16.081 --> 00:24:19.084
<i>If only you'd been born first.</i>

305
00:24:20.335 --> 00:24:22.671
My favorite son.

306
00:24:29.135 --> 00:24:32.347
(echoing) Is the duck not
to your liking. Your Grace?

307
00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:40.772
(normal) There's also
goose. if you'd prefer it.

308
00:24:42.607 --> 00:24:44.563
I like the goose. myself.

309
00:24:44.567 --> 00:24:46.778
(dinnerware clattering)

310
00:24:47.862 --> 00:24:50.115
(Alys pouring wine)

311
00:24:52.784 --> 00:24:54.448
Uh. I'm not hungry.

312
00:24:54.452 --> 00:24:56.617
Simon Strong: I was saying.
given the rather dire news

313
00:24:56.621 --> 00:24:58.456
from Rook's Rest...

314
00:24:59.457 --> 00:25:03.499
it appears the winds have shifted and
each side has suffered great loss.

315
00:25:03.503 --> 00:25:06.798
and will be unsure
of what is to follow.

316
00:25:08.174 --> 00:25:10.385
A good time. then. for
a show of strength.

317
00:25:11.136 --> 00:25:12.341
I believe Willem Blackwood

318
00:25:12.345 --> 00:25:14.639
is bringing House
Bracken to heel.

319
00:25:16.182 --> 00:25:19.394
We must ready the castle
to receive a great host.

320
00:25:21.688 --> 00:25:23.602
You seem sure of this.

321
00:25:23.606 --> 00:25:26.313
All men may be led. Ser Simon.

322
00:25:26.317 --> 00:25:28.028
Even Rivermen.

323
00:25:29.154 --> 00:25:32.907
'Tis a matter of showing them
whom it behooves them to follow.

324
00:25:34.367 --> 00:25:36.578
How does the work here progress?

325
00:25:36.911 --> 00:25:40.703
Oh. um... we're drawing
water for the kitchens

326
00:25:40.707 --> 00:25:43.289
- and lighting the forges.
- Very well.

327
00:25:43.293 --> 00:25:45.708
That is merely the
beginning. of course.

328
00:25:45.712 --> 00:25:47.501
The roof alone
has needed tending

329
00:25:47.505 --> 00:25:48.502
since the reign of Aenys.

330
00:25:48.506 --> 00:25:49.837
And the storerooms.

331
00:25:49.841 --> 00:25:51.009
And...

332
00:25:51.926 --> 00:25:54.346
and the Wailing
Tower. (chuckles)

333
00:25:55.013 --> 00:25:57.470
The bats have made the
corridors almost impassable

334
00:25:57.474 --> 00:25:59.517
with the quantity of their...

335
00:26:00.602 --> 00:26:02.020
Their shit.

336
00:26:04.397 --> 00:26:06.354
{\an8}I venture there are
smiths and armorers

337
00:26:06.358 --> 00:26:08.814
{\an8}to be found near
Nutton and Riverbend.

338
00:26:08.818 --> 00:26:10.858
{\an8}Well. send for them.
and levy the farmers

339
00:26:10.862 --> 00:26:12.906
from Antlers to High Heart.

340
00:26:13.239 --> 00:26:15.909
Task their huntsmen to
bring us meat and wood.

341
00:26:17.118 --> 00:26:19.742
Um. there is. of course.
the matter of payment.

342
00:26:19.746 --> 00:26:21.577
(clattering stops)

343
00:26:21.581 --> 00:26:26.044
After the. the tragedy
that befell his father...

344
00:26:26.419 --> 00:26:30.965
Larys transferred his family's
wealth to King's Landing.

345
00:26:32.217 --> 00:26:34.757
Is there any gold
left in your coffers?

346
00:26:34.761 --> 00:26:39.224
Enough to keep this small
establishment you see fed and warm.

347
00:26:40.225 --> 00:26:41.601
Relatively.

348
00:26:44.312 --> 00:26:47.687
I... I rather thought.
Your Grace. as

349
00:26:47.691 --> 00:26:51.107
emissary to the Queen

350
00:26:51.111 --> 00:26:55.027
that p-perhaps she could
provide the necessary coin

351
00:26:55.031 --> 00:26:57.659
- if you could only write to her.
- No.

352
00:26:58.576 --> 00:27:00.578
Harrenhal is my command.

353
00:27:01.162 --> 00:27:03.790
I shall guarantee
the payment myself.

354
00:27:04.916 --> 00:27:06.584
(mouths) Up. up.

355
00:27:09.587 --> 00:27:11.589
Very well. Your Grace.

356
00:27:12.090 --> 00:27:15.423
You should address
me as "my king."

357
00:27:15.427 --> 00:27:17.303
But you're the prince.

358
00:27:17.762 --> 00:27:19.927
What would you call the
husband of the queen?

359
00:27:19.931 --> 00:27:21.595
- Well. the king...
- Daemon: There it is. then.

360
00:27:21.599 --> 00:27:23.101
...consort.

361
00:27:24.310 --> 00:27:26.938
That last bit seems
unnecessary. don't you think?

362
00:27:29.482 --> 00:27:30.942
(sighing)

363
00:27:32.944 --> 00:27:35.109
Orwyle: The armor
was Valyrian steel.

364
00:27:35.113 --> 00:27:39.117
but His Grace suffered grievous
burns over much of his body.

365
00:27:40.243 --> 00:27:42.158
He has many broken bones.

366
00:27:42.162 --> 00:27:45.494
I fear there are
more injuries within.

367
00:27:45.498 --> 00:27:47.500
injuries we cannot see.

368
00:27:49.127 --> 00:27:51.334
(inhales) We are
grateful for your works.

369
00:27:51.338 --> 00:27:52.380
Grand Maester.

370
00:27:53.548 --> 00:27:55.967
- Has he woken?
- No.

371
00:27:57.635 --> 00:28:02.261
I must admit. I'm not
sure he will ever wake.

372
00:28:02.265 --> 00:28:05.639
I have plied my crafts
to their fullest extents.

373
00:28:05.643 --> 00:28:09.647
Our king's fate lies
with the gods now.

374
00:28:20.367 --> 00:28:22.369
A king cannot rule in his sleep.

375
00:28:23.495 --> 00:28:25.663
The realm will have
noticed his absence.

376
00:28:26.373 --> 00:28:28.583
Let them hear of his great
deeds at Rook's Rest.

377
00:28:30.085 --> 00:28:32.833
But now we must name a
regent to take his place

378
00:28:32.837 --> 00:28:34.506
until he recovers...

379
00:28:36.883 --> 00:28:38.093
or does not.

380
00:28:39.761 --> 00:28:42.134
A wise strategy. Your Grace.

381
00:28:42.138 --> 00:28:43.844
A regency will assure the people

382
00:28:43.848 --> 00:28:46.267
of the stability of the crown.

383
00:28:49.020 --> 00:28:52.148
Did you have a candidate
in mind. Your Grace?

384
00:28:52.691 --> 00:28:54.480
I myself served in this
role for my husband.

385
00:28:54.484 --> 00:28:56.023
I am well-prepared
to do it again.

386
00:28:56.027 --> 00:28:57.525
You played your part admirably

387
00:28:57.529 --> 00:28:59.151
in a time of peace. Your Grace.

388
00:28:59.155 --> 00:29:01.737
but circumstances have changed.

389
00:29:01.741 --> 00:29:03.489
(sarcastically) And
here I had forgotten.

390
00:29:03.493 --> 00:29:05.741
Ironrod: The king does
not lack for heirs.

391
00:29:05.745 --> 00:29:10.579
The obvious choice is his
immediate successor. Prince Aemond.

392
00:29:10.583 --> 00:29:12.039
Tyland Lannister: Agreed.

393
00:29:12.043 --> 00:29:13.712
Aemond is young.

394
00:29:15.088 --> 00:29:17.716
And his lack of restraint
has already cost us dearly.

395
00:29:27.267 --> 00:29:31.267
Orwyle: It is experience that
offers the surest path to security.

396
00:29:31.271 --> 00:29:34.395
Queen Alicent ably shouldered
the duties of the realm

397
00:29:34.399 --> 00:29:36.063
when her husband's
health failed him.

398
00:29:36.067 --> 00:29:37.440
Experience is valuable. yes.

399
00:29:37.444 --> 00:29:39.025
but the dowager
queen is a woman.

400
00:29:39.029 --> 00:29:42.111
I am no stranger to rule or
to sitting at this council.

401
00:29:42.115 --> 00:29:43.529
Aemond is a fearsome
dragon rider.

402
00:29:43.533 --> 00:29:45.031
His skill is best
employed in the field.

403
00:29:45.035 --> 00:29:47.783
but my experience is
needed here. at this table.

404
00:29:47.787 --> 00:29:50.244
No offense was meant.
Your Grace. but...

405
00:29:50.248 --> 00:29:54.419
- at a time when we must show strength.
- Lord Larys?

406
00:29:55.587 --> 00:29:57.922
I agree. Your Grace. It
must be Prince Aemond.

407
00:30:00.091 --> 00:30:02.423
What would it say if. in
response to Rhaenyra's crowning.

408
00:30:02.427 --> 00:30:04.679
we raised up a woman of our own?

409
00:30:07.432 --> 00:30:08.808
But. um...

410
00:30:10.518 --> 00:30:12.433
but the Hand speaks
for the king's voice.

411
00:30:12.437 --> 00:30:14.481
Ser Criston. what say you?

412
00:30:21.488 --> 00:30:23.698
Aemond is the next in line.

413
00:30:25.867 --> 00:30:27.285
It must be him.

414
00:30:31.956 --> 00:30:33.958
Aemond Targaryen:
It's agreed then.

415
00:30:55.480 --> 00:30:57.691
What is our standing
in the Riverlands?

416
00:30:59.234 --> 00:31:01.857
Tyland: Uh. the
banners of House Tully

417
00:31:01.861 --> 00:31:04.151
are in disarray. Your Grace.

418
00:31:04.155 --> 00:31:05.444
Prince Daemon has little hope

419
00:31:05.448 --> 00:31:07.947
of fielding an army
of any size. for now.

420
00:31:07.951 --> 00:31:09.657
(voices fading)

421
00:31:09.661 --> 00:31:11.701
Larys Strong: We would do well to
send word to young Oscar Tully.

422
00:31:11.705 --> 00:31:13.619
- (Alicent breathing heavily)
- It's only a matter of time

423
00:31:13.623 --> 00:31:15.955
before he inherits his
grandsire's mantle.

424
00:31:15.959 --> 00:31:17.999
Aemond: Tell me. Lord Strong.

425
00:31:18.003 --> 00:31:19.667
how I can trust the
counsel of a man

426
00:31:19.671 --> 00:31:21.210
who leaves the jewel
of the Riverlands

427
00:31:21.214 --> 00:31:23.675
to be plucked by our enemy?

428
00:31:27.345 --> 00:31:28.801
Your brother's host
can meet Daemon.

429
00:31:28.805 --> 00:31:30.177
He should quicken its pace

430
00:31:30.181 --> 00:31:31.303
and check the Rivermen

431
00:31:31.307 --> 00:31:32.888
while their banners
are in disarray.

432
00:31:32.892 --> 00:31:35.307
Tyland: I shall send
Lord Jason encouragement.

433
00:31:35.311 --> 00:31:38.019
- Aemond: What else?
- Orwyle: We might turn our attention

434
00:31:38.023 --> 00:31:40.521
to the smallfolk here
in King's Landing.

435
00:31:40.525 --> 00:31:43.024
They have grown weary of
the Sea Snake's blockade.

436
00:31:43.028 --> 00:31:45.192
Aemond: So have we all.

437
00:31:45.196 --> 00:31:46.485
Orwyle: Many are
fleeing the city.

438
00:31:46.489 --> 00:31:49.701
spreading word of
their fear and unrest.

439
00:31:50.118 --> 00:31:53.159
Aemond: Mm. then let
the gates be closed.

440
00:31:53.163 --> 00:31:55.369
â™ª

441
00:31:55.373 --> 00:31:57.872
No one is to leave or enter.
save with our consent.

442
00:31:57.876 --> 00:32:00.754
Merchants. so forth.

443
00:32:02.547 --> 00:32:05.004
(heavy breathing)

444
00:32:05.008 --> 00:32:07.715
(clearly) Go to your tasks.

445
00:32:07.719 --> 00:32:10.217
We shall meet again
at first light.

446
00:32:10.221 --> 00:32:14.059
Oh. and someone cut down
the fucking ratcatchers.

447
00:32:16.644 --> 00:32:18.059
(coughs)

448
00:32:18.063 --> 00:32:21.062
- (outside street chatter)
- (baby crying)

449
00:32:21.066 --> 00:32:23.318
Kat: The city's
safe no longer.

450
00:32:25.153 --> 00:32:27.610
There is no food.

451
00:32:27.614 --> 00:32:29.528
Our neighbors are
stealing from each other.

452
00:32:29.532 --> 00:32:30.905
We must get out.

453
00:32:30.909 --> 00:32:32.740
{\an8}And where would you have us go?

454
00:32:32.744 --> 00:32:35.038
North. maybe? South?

455
00:32:35.747 --> 00:32:37.870
For all we know. every road
leads into the dragons' teeth.

456
00:32:37.874 --> 00:32:40.168
Like the one they carted
through the streets?

457
00:32:41.002 --> 00:32:45.006
You think Rhaenyra will let
such an affront go unchallenged?

458
00:32:48.093 --> 00:32:50.883
We should make for Tumbleton.

459
00:32:50.887 --> 00:32:52.927
My brother will have room.

460
00:32:52.931 --> 00:32:54.766
You would have me turn beggar?

461
00:32:56.309 --> 00:32:57.936
(daughter groans)

462
00:33:00.814 --> 00:33:02.816
Are we not beggars already?

463
00:33:03.817 --> 00:33:05.481
Have you been paid
for those machines

464
00:33:05.485 --> 00:33:06.440
you were forced to build?

465
00:33:06.444 --> 00:33:08.109
The king has promised payment.

466
00:33:08.113 --> 00:33:10.990
(hushed) The king has lied!

467
00:33:14.786 --> 00:33:15.954
(coughs)

468
00:33:22.627 --> 00:33:24.462
By all means...

469
00:33:25.296 --> 00:33:28.675
stay and wait for his
empty promises. husband.

470
00:33:30.802 --> 00:33:33.638
With them. you can feed
the mouths of ghosts.

471
00:33:45.316 --> 00:33:47.318
(dog whimpering)

472
00:33:49.863 --> 00:33:51.865
(indistinct chatter)

473
00:33:58.830 --> 00:34:00.415
(body thuds)

474
00:34:13.011 --> 00:34:15.013
Presumed you'd be here.

475
00:34:15.430 --> 00:34:18.721
Seeing faithfully to the
Prince Regent's commands.

476
00:34:18.725 --> 00:34:20.848
Aemond is the next in line.

477
00:34:20.852 --> 00:34:23.851
- It is the order of things.
- You know what he is...

478
00:34:23.855 --> 00:34:25.899
what he has somehow become.

479
00:34:28.693 --> 00:34:30.066
Has your loyalty faded?

480
00:34:30.070 --> 00:34:32.026
Or does it flourish
only at night

481
00:34:32.030 --> 00:34:34.866
and flee the
sunrise like a moth?

482
00:34:38.620 --> 00:34:40.159
What I saw at Rook's Rest...

483
00:34:40.163 --> 00:34:43.375
What? What did you see?

484
00:34:47.545 --> 00:34:49.547
Their armor melted.

485
00:34:51.257 --> 00:34:53.885
There were men walking.
They were on fire.

486
00:34:57.305 --> 00:34:59.557
We have given the
war to the dragons.

487
00:35:01.101 --> 00:35:02.727
A dragon rider should lead us.

488
00:35:07.107 --> 00:35:09.438
And what of justice.
of temperance?

489
00:35:09.442 --> 00:35:12.487
Or is strength now
to be our only god?

490
00:35:17.909 --> 00:35:19.911
So you cast me aside.

491
00:35:21.079 --> 00:35:23.081
Have I not spared you?

492
00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:28.628
What we must do
now is... terrible.

493
00:35:30.588 --> 00:35:32.632
Will you preside over it?

494
00:35:33.258 --> 00:35:36.845
- Is this who you are. Alicent?
- I did not ask to be spared.

495
00:35:40.306 --> 00:35:42.434
And I did not give you
leave to speak my name.

496
00:35:48.356 --> 00:35:50.358
(loud chattering)

497
00:35:55.447 --> 00:35:56.781
gold cloak: Halt!

498
00:35:57.449 --> 00:35:59.451
(crowd shouting)

499
00:36:02.787 --> 00:36:03.997
Stay back!

500
00:36:05.790 --> 00:36:07.459
Towns person: We've
got to get out!

501
00:36:08.293 --> 00:36:09.794
Gold cloak: Somebody get him!

502
00:36:10.545 --> 00:36:12.668
Stay back! No!

503
00:36:12.672 --> 00:36:15.129
Holdfast. hold fast!

504
00:36:15.133 --> 00:36:17.344
- (shouting. fighting)
- Stay back! Hold!

505
00:36:22.140 --> 00:36:23.308
Back!

506
00:36:24.351 --> 00:36:27.312
Disperse. disperse!

507
00:36:28.480 --> 00:36:30.936
By order of Aemond Targaryen.

508
00:36:30.940 --> 00:36:33.773
Prince Regent and
Protector of the Realm...

509
00:36:33.777 --> 00:36:36.275
- Aemond?
- Does he mean the king?

510
00:36:36.279 --> 00:36:38.652
- I don't know.
- You cannot keep us here!

511
00:36:38.656 --> 00:36:41.614
- You are ordered to return to your homes!
- We want meat!

512
00:36:41.618 --> 00:36:43.199
- Meat!
- Meat!

513
00:36:43.203 --> 00:36:44.913
(shouting)

514
00:36:51.211 --> 00:36:53.376
(crowd. gold cloaks clamoring)

515
00:36:53.380 --> 00:36:54.839
gold cloak: Stay back!

516
00:36:57.050 --> 00:36:58.677
(grumbles)

517
00:37:02.847 --> 00:37:06.059
Forrest Frey: Our Lord Grover Tully
has not declared for Rhaenyra.

518
00:37:07.268 --> 00:37:09.392
It means death to bare
steel against your liege.

519
00:37:09.396 --> 00:37:11.690
as I'm sure my prince is aware.

520
00:37:13.191 --> 00:37:15.402
And against your queen?

521
00:37:17.612 --> 00:37:18.613
Hm?

522
00:37:22.450 --> 00:37:27.201
(sighs) Jason Lannister
is marshaling to the west.

523
00:37:27.205 --> 00:37:29.290
We need to check him
before he reaches Riverrun.

524
00:37:30.208 --> 00:37:32.206
That requires passage.

525
00:37:32.210 --> 00:37:34.667
And if Stark's army is too slow?

526
00:37:34.671 --> 00:37:36.419
The wind's rising.

527
00:37:36.423 --> 00:37:38.087
Winter is nigh upon us.

528
00:37:38.091 --> 00:37:39.755
Our hesitance does not lie

529
00:37:39.759 --> 00:37:41.882
in Rhaenyra as Queen.

530
00:37:41.886 --> 00:37:45.306
nor in the ruminations
of Lord Tully. the oaf.

531
00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:49.056
Our fear lies in Vhagar.

532
00:37:49.060 --> 00:37:52.101
You fear a dragon leagues away

533
00:37:52.105 --> 00:37:54.770
when mine own sits
outside your walls?

534
00:37:54.774 --> 00:37:56.818
(wind blowing)

535
00:37:59.070 --> 00:38:02.407
- Do you offer us your protection?
- I do.

536
00:38:08.997 --> 00:38:10.999
And the protection of my uncle.

537
00:38:12.250 --> 00:38:16.417
And Daemon. I'm sure.
has consented to this?

538
00:38:16.421 --> 00:38:18.544
He will do as his
queen commands.

539
00:38:18.548 --> 00:38:20.463
That does lend us some comfort.

540
00:38:20.467 --> 00:38:21.922
Though it occurs
to me that dragons

541
00:38:21.926 --> 00:38:25.263
- cannot be in two places at once.
- Or three.

542
00:38:28.183 --> 00:38:30.018
What do you want?

543
00:38:32.312 --> 00:38:36.270
Larys Strong has been
relieved of his castle.

544
00:38:36.274 --> 00:38:39.361
Does the queen intend
to raise up a new lord?

545
00:38:43.823 --> 00:38:45.283
You want Harrenhal.

546
00:38:56.628 --> 00:39:00.382
(light. tense music playing)

547
00:39:04.177 --> 00:39:09.140
For that... my mother will
want more than your crossing.

548
00:39:10.892 --> 00:39:12.894
What does Her Grace desire?

549
00:39:15.522 --> 00:39:17.732
Bent knees.

550
00:39:19.818 --> 00:39:21.820
(music intensifies)

551
00:39:42.882 --> 00:39:45.131
(music fades out)

552
00:39:45.135 --> 00:39:47.846
(indistinct chatter)

553
00:39:48.680 --> 00:39:50.890
(screams echoing)

554
00:39:56.855 --> 00:39:59.524
(screaming subsides)

555
00:40:00.692 --> 00:40:02.736
(indistinct chatter)

556
00:40:11.578 --> 00:40:12.787
Daemon: Up.

557
00:40:13.455 --> 00:40:15.202
Alys Rivers: You were
born to wield a sword.

558
00:40:15.206 --> 00:40:18.251
but not so much an axe. perhaps.

559
00:40:19.461 --> 00:40:21.083
Daemon: There are others
who would sit idle

560
00:40:21.087 --> 00:40:23.336
and wait for their claims
to be brought to them.

561
00:40:23.340 --> 00:40:26.672
- That is not my way.
- Does splitting firewood justify what's followed you here?

562
00:40:26.676 --> 00:40:28.716
Let it not be said
that Daemon Targaryen

563
00:40:28.720 --> 00:40:31.052
failed to dirty his
hands in this war.

564
00:40:31.056 --> 00:40:32.932
Oh. let me see them.

565
00:40:34.059 --> 00:40:35.931
- Sit.
- Daemon: Ah.

566
00:40:35.935 --> 00:40:37.228
Sit!

567
00:40:40.899 --> 00:40:44.357
(sighs) I hear strange
things from Bracken land.

568
00:40:44.361 --> 00:40:47.405
from Stone Hedge and
Lambswold and Mory.

569
00:40:48.406 --> 00:40:50.529
There's news. then?

570
00:40:50.533 --> 00:40:51.743
News?

571
00:40:52.911 --> 00:40:53.912
No.

572
00:40:56.081 --> 00:40:58.871
What I hear. I hear in the wind.

573
00:40:58.875 --> 00:41:01.920
- (screams echoing)
- Cries of anguish.

574
00:41:03.838 --> 00:41:05.920
Children being taken
from their mothers.

575
00:41:05.924 --> 00:41:09.882
men coming home to find
their doors unlatched...

576
00:41:09.886 --> 00:41:12.093
their wives carried away.

577
00:41:12.097 --> 00:41:14.261
(screaming subsides)

578
00:41:14.265 --> 00:41:16.476
War is a terrible thing.

579
00:41:17.018 --> 00:41:19.600
This is not war.

580
00:41:19.604 --> 00:41:22.269
These are crimes
against the innocent.

581
00:41:22.273 --> 00:41:24.563
that any upright
man would repudiate.

582
00:41:24.567 --> 00:41:27.108
Surely you haven't mistaken
me for an upright man.

583
00:41:27.112 --> 00:41:29.110
(Alys chuckles)

584
00:41:29.114 --> 00:41:32.780
The Brackens had their
chance to do as I required.

585
00:41:32.784 --> 00:41:34.907
They will perhaps think
better of their decision

586
00:41:34.911 --> 00:41:38.123
if their children's
lives are staked on it.

587
00:41:39.457 --> 00:41:41.835
Is that the kind of
army you would raise?

588
00:41:42.836 --> 00:41:45.501
Men who hate you...

589
00:41:45.505 --> 00:41:47.294
who serve you under duress?

590
00:41:47.298 --> 00:41:50.423
Well. once they agree to serve
me. I'll treat them fairly.

591
00:41:50.427 --> 00:41:51.674
Set an example for the rest

592
00:41:51.678 --> 00:41:53.801
of the Riverlands to follow.

593
00:41:53.805 --> 00:41:56.303
And once again. in
the name of power.

594
00:41:56.307 --> 00:41:59.144
it's the weak and the
women who must endure.

595
00:42:01.980 --> 00:42:04.816
That fool. Aegon. is
unlike to survive.

596
00:42:06.901 --> 00:42:09.195
The realm will suffer
if Aemond One-Eye rules.

597
00:42:10.739 --> 00:42:12.323
You should pray
you never meet him.

598
00:42:12.907 --> 00:42:15.281
He will cut you down soon
as wish you good-day.

599
00:42:15.285 --> 00:42:16.824
I'd heard the same
thing about you.

600
00:42:16.828 --> 00:42:17.992
But I'll cross you no further.

601
00:42:17.996 --> 00:42:19.452
I'm sure your tactics
are. after all.

602
00:42:19.456 --> 00:42:21.328
approved by the queen.

603
00:42:21.332 --> 00:42:24.336
(tense music playing)

604
00:42:26.838 --> 00:42:29.049
She cannot succeed. Alys.

605
00:42:29.716 --> 00:42:31.964
Even if I willed it to be so.

606
00:42:31.968 --> 00:42:34.050
The people who support her
will not be led by her.

607
00:42:34.054 --> 00:42:36.177
They look to a man for strength.

608
00:42:36.181 --> 00:42:37.345
Who's better suited to it?

609
00:42:37.349 --> 00:42:39.805
The Hightowers with
their scheming?

610
00:42:39.809 --> 00:42:42.020
Or Viserys's first true heir?

611
00:42:43.188 --> 00:42:45.644
When I take King's Landing...

612
00:42:45.648 --> 00:42:47.188
Rhaenyra is welcome
to join me there

613
00:42:47.192 --> 00:42:49.690
and take her place by my side.

614
00:42:49.694 --> 00:42:53.740
King and queen...
ruling together.

615
00:42:54.366 --> 00:42:57.031
- And if you lose?
- Then I'll be dead.

616
00:42:57.035 --> 00:42:59.408
and none of this
will be my problem.

617
00:42:59.412 --> 00:43:02.703
It's a pity. don't you think.
that you never knew your mother?

618
00:43:02.707 --> 00:43:04.709
â™ª

619
00:43:06.252 --> 00:43:08.421
Simon: A message. Your Grace.

620
00:43:10.090 --> 00:43:11.091
Uh...

621
00:43:13.551 --> 00:43:16.384
uh. fresh news from Stone Hedge.

622
00:43:16.388 --> 00:43:18.678
The Blackwoods have
overwhelmed the Brackens.

623
00:43:18.682 --> 00:43:22.060
and. uh. Lord Amos has
pledged his banner to you.

624
00:43:22.435 --> 00:43:24.646
House Bracken is yours.

625
00:43:26.064 --> 00:43:28.733
Call Ser Willem here so that
I might congratulate him.

626
00:43:29.150 --> 00:43:31.778
The Blackwoods will be
feted in these halls.

627
00:43:32.904 --> 00:43:35.907
- (bird cawing)
- (dog barking)

628
00:43:38.660 --> 00:43:40.662
(waves crashing)

629
00:43:43.248 --> 00:43:45.250
I sought you at High Tide.

630
00:43:45.959 --> 00:43:48.253
I was surprised when
they said you were here.

631
00:43:49.421 --> 00:43:51.423
My castle is a tomb.

632
00:43:52.757 --> 00:43:54.926
Empty. Haunted.

633
00:43:55.760 --> 00:43:58.680
I am sad to have missed
its highest days.

634
00:43:59.681 --> 00:44:01.053
I imagine your Hall of Nine

635
00:44:01.057 --> 00:44:03.431
filled with lords and kings.

636
00:44:03.435 --> 00:44:06.521
all eager to treat with the
legendary Lord of the Tides.

637
00:44:08.440 --> 00:44:09.437
The wealth you brought back

638
00:44:09.441 --> 00:44:10.813
from Yi Ti and Asshai.

639
00:44:10.817 --> 00:44:14.112
inspiring awe and envy.

640
00:44:16.531 --> 00:44:18.533
I wonder if any of them
knew it was all for her.

641
00:44:27.667 --> 00:44:29.999
Queen Rhaenyra wishes
to name you Hand.

642
00:44:30.003 --> 00:44:31.671
(Corlys sighs)

643
00:44:33.381 --> 00:44:37.218
Even the death of my wife
does not content her.

644
00:44:39.554 --> 00:44:41.806
Has she not asked
enough of my house?

645
00:44:42.307 --> 00:44:45.973
It is a sign of
her great esteem.

646
00:44:45.977 --> 00:44:48.017
Or does she think the
position will compensate me

647
00:44:48.021 --> 00:44:49.314
for my loss?

648
00:44:50.523 --> 00:44:52.855
Pledge your peace to
King's Landing. then.

649
00:44:52.859 --> 00:44:55.153
They will accept
it most gleefully.

650
00:44:57.822 --> 00:45:00.408
Rather I would sail into
the West and be lost.

651
00:45:01.576 --> 00:45:03.616
You have done so before.

652
00:45:03.620 --> 00:45:06.373
at great cost to yourself
and those who loved you.

653
00:45:08.917 --> 00:45:12.291
Rhaenys was not
only your wife...

654
00:45:12.295 --> 00:45:15.461
not a thing to be
taken from you.

655
00:45:15.465 --> 00:45:18.093
She was a Targaryen princess.

656
00:45:18.843 --> 00:45:20.174
The Queen Who Never Was.

657
00:45:20.178 --> 00:45:22.885
And she flew to Rook's
Rest of her own will.

658
00:45:22.889 --> 00:45:25.346
- In defense of her kin.
- And she died.

659
00:45:25.350 --> 00:45:28.057
She died as she would
have wished to die...

660
00:45:28.061 --> 00:45:31.686
with honor. in dragon fire.

661
00:45:31.690 --> 00:45:33.024
The way my mother chose...

662
00:45:35.360 --> 00:45:38.196
and the way I myself
wish to meet my end.

663
00:45:42.283 --> 00:45:45.324
(solemn music playing)

664
00:45:45.328 --> 00:45:48.536
I grieve my grandmother
who loved me

665
00:45:48.540 --> 00:45:52.039
but I carry her on with me.

666
00:45:52.043 --> 00:45:56.339
I will see Rhaenyra ascend the
Iron Throne. as Rhaenys wished.

667
00:45:56.923 --> 00:45:58.925
As Rhaenys herself should have.

668
00:46:01.720 --> 00:46:04.389
You yourself may
do as you see fit.

669
00:46:07.934 --> 00:46:09.557
Granddaughter.

670
00:46:09.561 --> 00:46:11.604
â™ª

671
00:46:17.068 --> 00:46:20.113
I would make you my heir.

672
00:46:21.740 --> 00:46:23.742
I am blood and fire.

673
00:46:24.284 --> 00:46:27.287
Driftmark must pass
to salt and sea.

674
00:46:35.795 --> 00:46:38.006
(music fades out)

675
00:46:46.097 --> 00:46:47.265
Your Grace.

676
00:46:50.935 --> 00:46:52.270
You were correct...

677
00:46:53.938 --> 00:46:56.524
in saying our best hope
of an army is with Daemon.

678
00:46:59.194 --> 00:47:04.616
And I have. perhaps. erred in
waiting for him to prove himself.

679
00:47:06.659 --> 00:47:08.661
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

680
00:47:10.455 --> 00:47:12.832
Are you removing me
from your council?

681
00:47:14.376 --> 00:47:15.835
Ser Alfred...

682
00:47:16.795 --> 00:47:20.294
I-I-I will not deny you have
tried my patience of late.

683
00:47:20.298 --> 00:47:22.588
or that I would prefer a council

684
00:47:22.592 --> 00:47:24.131
more inclined to
champion their queen.

685
00:47:24.135 --> 00:47:25.804
but... (inhales)

686
00:47:26.888 --> 00:47:30.262
you and your house
served my father well.

687
00:47:30.266 --> 00:47:33.311
and I know you will never
accept the Hightower claim.

688
00:47:34.979 --> 00:47:37.565
Not while I live. Your Grace.

689
00:47:40.402 --> 00:47:44.318
We cannot challenge King's
Landing without the Riverlands

690
00:47:44.322 --> 00:47:47.992
but I will not send a message by
raven for Daemon to disregard.

691
00:47:50.328 --> 00:47:55.166
I ask you to...
reason with him.

692
00:47:56.501 --> 00:48:01.089
Find out his state of
mind and his intentions.

693
00:48:03.008 --> 00:48:05.506
Intentions?

694
00:48:05.510 --> 00:48:09.014
Whether he means to raise a
host for me or for himself.

695
00:48:12.017 --> 00:48:13.389
He would not dare.

696
00:48:13.393 --> 00:48:16.104
(scoffs) Have you known
Daemon to lack in daring?

697
00:48:17.689 --> 00:48:19.478
Go now with haste.

698
00:48:19.482 --> 00:48:22.110
I'll send good men to
see to your safety.

699
00:48:29.701 --> 00:48:32.370
Have you any message for him?

700
00:48:36.291 --> 00:48:39.544
Tell him I would much like to
finish our last conversation.

701
00:48:42.047 --> 00:48:43.214
Your Grace.

702
00:48:50.805 --> 00:48:53.433
{\an8}- (rumbling)
- (water dripping)

703
00:48:54.726 --> 00:48:56.728
{\an8}(eerie warbling)

704
00:49:04.778 --> 00:49:06.404
{\an8}(footsteps approach)

705
00:49:14.621 --> 00:49:16.623
(knocking on door)

706
00:49:19.584 --> 00:49:21.002
Simon: Your Grace.

707
00:49:22.629 --> 00:49:24.255
(panting)

708
00:49:24.798 --> 00:49:29.010
What is it. Ser Simon? Is
the pudding now served?

709
00:49:29.678 --> 00:49:32.093
The Riverlords have
come. Your Grace.

710
00:49:32.097 --> 00:49:35.016
- They wish an audience.
- Now?

711
00:49:35.600 --> 00:49:38.019
- What godless hour is it?
- The wolf.

712
00:49:38.770 --> 00:49:40.605
They are demanding
to speak presently.

713
00:49:42.982 --> 00:49:45.985
(tense music playing)

714
00:49:59.332 --> 00:50:01.334
â™ª

715
00:50:11.636 --> 00:50:14.969
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

716
00:50:14.973 --> 00:50:16.178
Or failing that. in proper fear

717
00:50:16.182 --> 00:50:18.226
of your Targaryen master.

718
00:50:20.020 --> 00:50:25.104
Is there some reason you feel
free to wake a king in his bed?

719
00:50:25.108 --> 00:50:27.648
Or shall I now begin
your education?

720
00:50:27.652 --> 00:50:29.275
House Bracken

721
00:50:29.279 --> 00:50:32.987
have been brought to heel at
the hands of Willem Blackwood.

722
00:50:32.991 --> 00:50:36.323
- That news is stale.
- (chuckles) Yes.

723
00:50:36.327 --> 00:50:38.284
There have been.
um. complications.

724
00:50:38.288 --> 00:50:40.828
The sacred septs
on Bracken lands

725
00:50:40.832 --> 00:50:44.165
- were looted and burned.
- As were the fields and farms.

726
00:50:44.169 --> 00:50:45.791
The livestock was stolen

727
00:50:45.795 --> 00:50:47.335
and our peasants
put to the sword.

728
00:50:47.339 --> 00:50:49.962
They pursued the women
and the children.

729
00:50:49.966 --> 00:50:51.505
There were works of barbarity.

730
00:50:51.509 --> 00:50:55.468
Punishing Bracken for his own
treasons is one thing. aye.

731
00:50:55.472 --> 00:50:58.179
- But these other acts.
- The Brackens were given their chance.

732
00:50:58.183 --> 00:51:00.681
- They would not see reason.
- The Blackwoods have exploited

733
00:51:00.685 --> 00:51:02.683
the war for the crown
to visit atrocities

734
00:51:02.687 --> 00:51:05.186
- upon their old rivals.
- Piper: I have seen my fair share of their quarrels.

735
00:51:05.190 --> 00:51:06.645
and I tell you. there
is no honor in a fight

736
00:51:06.649 --> 00:51:08.689
- such as this.
- Honor? What of common decency?

737
00:51:08.693 --> 00:51:10.983
These beasts proudly carried

738
00:51:10.987 --> 00:51:12.818
the banner of House Targaryen.

739
00:51:12.822 --> 00:51:14.699
Red dragon on black.

740
00:51:17.285 --> 00:51:19.287
(eerie warbling)

741
00:51:21.289 --> 00:51:24.542
female voice: A terrible war
is being fought in these lands.

742
00:51:28.046 --> 00:51:30.048
Have you looked after our girls?

743
00:51:32.300 --> 00:51:35.303
(ominous music playing)

744
00:51:37.555 --> 00:51:39.595
Darry: We should've expected
nothing more from a man

745
00:51:39.599 --> 00:51:41.681
who ordered the
slaughter of a child

746
00:51:41.685 --> 00:51:43.144
in his mother's arms.

747
00:51:45.397 --> 00:51:48.688
That is a lie. And I will have the
man who told it brought before me.

748
00:51:48.692 --> 00:51:53.321
Well. your man is half
the kingdom. my prince.

749
00:51:56.282 --> 00:51:58.284
Know this. interloper:

750
00:51:58.993 --> 00:52:01.867
the Riverlands are
an ancient place.

751
00:52:01.871 --> 00:52:05.746
watched closely by the
eyes of old gods and new.

752
00:52:05.750 --> 00:52:07.707
And dragon or no.

753
00:52:07.711 --> 00:52:10.922
we shall not raise our
banners for a tyrant.

754
00:52:14.175 --> 00:52:17.178
(tense music playing)

755
00:52:28.773 --> 00:52:30.775
â™ª

756
00:52:52.881 --> 00:52:54.883
(indistinct chatter)

757
00:52:56.801 --> 00:52:58.803
â™ª

758
00:53:16.738 --> 00:53:18.944
â™ª

759
00:53:18.948 --> 00:53:22.827
- Move along. lass.
- I have an errand... for the lady Mysaria.

760
00:53:24.037 --> 00:53:26.160
I thought she was dead.

761
00:53:26.164 --> 00:53:28.375
Would she die without
collecting her due?

762
00:53:30.043 --> 00:53:31.878
I must see an old friend.

763
00:53:33.672 --> 00:53:35.674
Most people want out these days.

764
00:53:38.927 --> 00:53:40.929
â™ª

765
00:53:49.062 --> 00:53:51.064
â™ª

766
00:53:58.113 --> 00:53:59.739
(rain pattering)

767
00:54:05.078 --> 00:54:07.789
- (indistinct chatter)
- (thunder rumbling)

768
00:54:17.716 --> 00:54:19.718
(music softens)

769
00:54:20.927 --> 00:54:21.924
Elinda.

770
00:54:21.928 --> 00:54:24.010
(wind blowing)

771
00:54:24.014 --> 00:54:27.058
(pensive music playing)

772
00:54:29.269 --> 00:54:31.271
(deep breathing)

773
00:54:46.661 --> 00:54:48.284
(thunder rumbling)

774
00:54:48.288 --> 00:54:51.332
(tense music playing)

775
00:54:53.251 --> 00:54:55.837
(unsettling vocalizing)

776
00:55:06.097 --> 00:55:08.099
â™ª

777
00:55:13.772 --> 00:55:15.774
Was it worth the price?

778
00:55:22.364 --> 00:55:24.366
(shallow breathing)

779
00:55:28.370 --> 00:55:29.992
(thunder continues)

780
00:55:29.996 --> 00:55:33.041
(solemn music playing)

781
00:55:56.314 --> 00:55:58.316
â™ª

782
00:56:03.655 --> 00:56:05.657
(door opens)

783
00:56:06.825 --> 00:56:08.493
{\an8}(hoarsely) Mummy.

784
00:56:11.746 --> 00:56:13.748
â™ª

785
00:56:19.170 --> 00:56:20.793
(footstep approach)

786
00:56:20.797 --> 00:56:23.008
(music fades out)

787
00:56:25.677 --> 00:56:27.053
Prince Jacaerys. Your Grace.

788
00:56:44.529 --> 00:56:46.740
(distant dragon grumbles)

789
00:56:51.870 --> 00:56:53.246
Visenya.

790
00:56:54.247 --> 00:56:59.711
Vhagar's first rider. and the
first wielder of Dark Sister.

791
00:57:01.463 --> 00:57:03.836
I hope you do not mean
to use her as an example.

792
00:57:03.840 --> 00:57:05.504
Why shouldn't I?

793
00:57:05.508 --> 00:57:07.719
W... It was a long time ago.

794
00:57:17.979 --> 00:57:20.231
What is the mood at the Twins?

795
00:57:21.816 --> 00:57:24.069
Did his lordship quibble?

796
00:57:26.571 --> 00:57:30.158
He wishes for the Freys
to be granted Harrenhal.

797
00:57:31.659 --> 00:57:33.912
At war's end. Assuming.

798
00:57:36.664 --> 00:57:38.412
I'm proud of you. Jace.

799
00:57:38.416 --> 00:57:40.669
You have done our
cause a great service.

800
00:57:43.171 --> 00:57:45.924
Then. why do you look angry?

801
00:57:52.681 --> 00:57:54.303
(sighs)

802
00:57:54.307 --> 00:57:57.306
You chafed at being
prevented from action.

803
00:57:57.310 --> 00:58:00.101
Imagine my lot. I'm a
dragon rider as well.

804
00:58:00.105 --> 00:58:02.941
with a war being fought
over my ascension.

805
00:58:04.109 --> 00:58:06.111
And yet. I must wait here...

806
00:58:07.112 --> 00:58:09.485
always prudent...

807
00:58:09.489 --> 00:58:10.945
sending others to fight

808
00:58:10.949 --> 00:58:13.243
and be felled in my name.

809
00:58:13.785 --> 00:58:15.954
Even you have managed
to do your part.

810
00:58:16.621 --> 00:58:18.786
Jacaerys Velaryon:
You are the queen...

811
00:58:18.790 --> 00:58:20.121
the tie that binds us.

812
00:58:20.125 --> 00:58:21.789
- No harm can come to you.
- And you are my son.

813
00:58:21.793 --> 00:58:23.837
and I did not give
you leave to go.

814
00:58:25.964 --> 00:58:28.633
You do not give me
leave to go to anything.

815
00:58:29.009 --> 00:58:30.339
But who else is there?
Rhaenys is dead.

816
00:58:30.343 --> 00:58:32.174
and Baela cannot bear
the burden alone.

817
00:58:32.178 --> 00:58:34.802
And when Aemond comes
hunting for you?

818
00:58:34.806 --> 00:58:37.179
Your dragon is young.

819
00:58:37.183 --> 00:58:39.227
Will you fly before
Vhagar as Luke did?

820
00:58:46.192 --> 00:58:48.028
Perhaps Daemon could...

821
00:58:51.531 --> 00:58:54.196
Daemon is not here.

822
00:58:54.200 --> 00:58:56.494
And Aemond now rules
in King's Landing.

823
00:58:58.038 --> 00:59:02.163
- Is Aegon dead?
- Dead or alive. we have no answer for Vhagar.

824
00:59:02.167 --> 00:59:05.378
Aemond will not wait long to press
his advantage. And then what?

825
00:59:07.881 --> 00:59:09.670
I have done all I can from here.

826
00:59:09.674 --> 00:59:12.673
sent my messages.
invoked my alliances.

827
00:59:12.677 --> 00:59:14.846
But if all else fails.
it is I who must fight.

828
00:59:16.765 --> 00:59:19.805
Vhagar is big. but
Syrax is quicker.

829
00:59:19.809 --> 00:59:24.230
- So was Meleys.
- Meleys fought two dragons and one of them is slain.

830
00:59:25.899 --> 00:59:27.313
Shall I fight for my birthright?

831
00:59:27.317 --> 00:59:29.944
Or shall I wait here until
we are all destroyed?

832
00:59:35.784 --> 00:59:37.702
I need dragons.

833
00:59:41.206 --> 00:59:44.167
We have no dearth of dragons.

834
00:59:45.043 --> 00:59:48.042
We have two large enough
to stand against Vhagar.

835
00:59:48.046 --> 00:59:51.420
They are called
Vermithor and Silverwing

836
00:59:51.424 --> 00:59:52.880
and they sleep just
beneath our feet.

837
00:59:52.884 --> 00:59:54.173
Yes. and if only
they had riders.

838
00:59:54.177 --> 00:59:56.221
none could stand against me.

839
00:59:56.930 --> 01:00:00.141
I would go forth in strength
and not from necessity.

840
01:00:01.559 --> 01:00:02.932
There is Rhaena.

841
01:00:02.936 --> 01:00:05.980
(scoffs) Who nearly lost her
life in her last attempt.

842
01:00:07.482 --> 01:00:09.484
I would not risk it again.

843
01:00:15.407 --> 01:00:18.410
There are those of our
line who never ruled.

844
01:00:19.285 --> 01:00:22.743
Those who married into
other noble houses.

845
01:00:22.747 --> 01:00:25.621
their children born
with other names.

846
01:00:25.625 --> 01:00:29.250
A generation ago. or more.
Their blood would be thin.

847
01:00:29.254 --> 01:00:32.044
And yet...

848
01:00:32.048 --> 01:00:36.257
A dragon will only accept a
dragon lord to ride it. (Sighs)

849
01:00:36.261 --> 01:00:40.261
- Or so say the histories.
- (chuckles) Valyrian histories.

850
01:00:40.265 --> 01:00:42.221
Written to gild us in glory.

851
01:00:42.225 --> 01:00:43.852
(chuckles)

852
01:00:45.145 --> 01:00:47.772
Are you suggesting we put
a Mallister on a dragon?

853
01:00:48.356 --> 01:00:51.776
- A Tarly?
- It's better than death and defeat.

854
01:00:57.782 --> 01:01:01.282
There are records here.
surely. of our line

855
01:01:01.286 --> 01:01:03.576
and of those who fell out of it.

856
01:01:03.580 --> 01:01:06.624
(intense music playing)

857
01:01:11.004 --> 01:01:12.668
There could be scores of them.

858
01:01:12.672 --> 01:01:14.132
(exhales)

859
01:01:20.305 --> 01:01:22.140
It's a mad thought.

860
01:01:25.018 --> 01:01:27.020
â™ª

861
01:01:31.524 --> 01:01:33.735
(music fades out)

862
01:01:38.406 --> 01:01:41.409
â™ª

863
01:02:08.937 --> 01:02:10.939
â™ª

864
01:02:46.224 --> 01:02:48.435
(music fades out)
